WEBVTT

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:05.120
This year, in the midst of many challenges, we have been so grateful for you, our community.

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:10.800
You've continued to show up in so many different ways, even as the ways we work with and live have

00:00:10.800 --> 00:00:16.240
changed. You've used data to answer questions important to you, written insightful code,

00:00:16.240 --> 00:00:20.559
helped people learn and continue to share everything you do with your communities,

00:00:20.559 --> 00:00:26.400
co-workers, neighbours, family and friends. Thank you for your kindness, your curiosity

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:30.879
in bringing all of you to the ways that you work with and share about data.

00:00:30.879 --> 00:00:33.200
From RStudio Open Source, thank you.

00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:40.799
Thank you.

00:00:40.799 --> 00:00:41.599
Thank you.

00:00:41.599 --> 00:00:43.040
Thank you very much.

00:00:43.040 --> 00:00:43.540
Thank you.

00:00:44.480 --> 00:00:45.439
Thank you.

00:00:45.439 --> 00:00:46.320
Thank you.

00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:47.360
Thank you.

00:00:47.360 --> 00:00:47.860
Thank you.

00:00:48.720 --> 00:00:49.360
Thank you.

00:00:49.360 --> 00:00:52.000
A big thank you to the entire Open Source community.

00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:54.340
Thank you.

00:00:55.040 --> 00:00:55.540
Thank you.

00:00:56.639 --> 00:00:57.439
Thank you.

00:00:57.439 --> 00:01:00.880
Hey, you're using the things we made and I really appreciate that. Thank you.

00:01:01.599 --> 00:01:02.099
Merci.

00:01:03.119 --> 00:01:03.619
Thank you.

00:01:04.559 --> 00:01:05.839
You want to say thank you?

00:01:06.959 --> 00:01:07.459
Thank you.

00:01:11.279 --> 00:01:11.839
Thank you.

00:01:11.839 --> 00:01:12.339
Thank you.

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:13.760
Thank you.

00:01:13.760 --> 00:01:21.279
Thank you for all the ways you contribute and share.

